<h2>Setting Up the Trip Online</h2>
d41 2
a42 3
<p>Outdoors at UVA is run almost completely online.  If you would like to lead a
Club trip, you must use the website to create the trip online.  If you are a
first-timer, you must e-mail the officers at
d44 4
a47 23
order to get trip leader privileges on the website.  Once you have privileges,
you will see some new links, and setting up a trip is as simple as following the
directions from that point.  Please e-mail the officers with your questions
about what to say in the description, fees, etc etc.</p>

<h2>Trip Finances</h2>

<p>During the school year, Outdoors at UVA will pay for all the gas, lodging,
and food on a Club trip.  The club operates on a reimbursal system &mdash; so
whatever you buy for a trip, keep the receipts to get reimbursed.  The club will
pay the following for meals:</p>

<ul>
 <li>$2/person for breakfast</li>
 <li>$4/person for lunch </li>
 <li>$6/person for dinner </li>
</ul>

<p>If a member spends more than this on a meal, then the member needs to pay for
the difference.  In order to get reimbursed for gas, you must print off a gas
receipt form and have all drivers sign the form when you give them money for
gas.  Once the trip is over, you can turn in any receipts for food and lodging,
along with the gas receipt form, to an officer to receive reimbursement.</p>
